cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.IR, cs.DC, cs.NE 

The paper discusses an algorithm for multitemporal and multiband registration of remotely sensed data, which involves image processing and computer vision techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.GR (Graphics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with finding optimal transformation models and resampling transformed imagery, which falls under the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper mentions the implementation of operational software, which could be related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
